tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: All results are within or close to normal ranges, except for mildly elevated chloride and slightly low total cholesterol, both of which are not clinically significant in isolation. HbA1c is at the upper end of normal, suggesting monitoring for prediabetes. Renal function, electrolytes, and lipid profile are otherwise unremarkable. No acute laboratory concerns.
